description: A large sign hangs in the room:
{W|{y    This maze is designed to be a deathtrap. If you are able  {W  |
{W|{y    to escape with your life, you may consider yourself        {W |
{W|{y    lucky. There are great rewards to be had, as well as       {W |
{W|{y    great dangers. You have a time limit inside, based upon    {W |
{W|  {y  your physical well-being. You will NOT be transported      {W |
{W|{y    out, and you will NOT be saved by an immortal. This is     {W |
{W| {y   your first, last, and only warning. Inside the maze, it    {W |
{W| {y   is no_recall and no_magic. You may not enter the maze if   {W |
{W| {y   a corpse of yours exists in the realms. Either find a      {W |
{W| {y   friend you trust to hold your equipment, or suck it up     {W |
{W| {y   and take a risk. You will be unable to heal while in the   {W |
{W|  {y  maze, by any magical or mundane means. By entering the     {W |
{W|  {y  maze, you accept these risks, and pledge not to whine.     {W |
{W|  {y  If you whine, you lose your character. Having brief mode   {W |
{W| {y   on is no excuse, not paying attention is no excuse. Once   {W |
{W|{y    again - first, last, and only warning.                     {W |
{W|{y                                -Epsilon T. {bM{Boo{Dnsh{Bad{be{y, Esq. {W    |

description: You pass through the portal to find yourself in a small area on
the moon, which Mystra has created for Epsilon, allowing for quiet
contemplation.  It appears that Epsilon takes a slightly more active
hand in mortal affairs than his goddess.  The proud and lonely silence
of Mare Imbrium surrounds you, as you gaze upon the sterile splendor
of the moon.  All around is the velvet curtain of night, studded with
a thousand gleaming jewels.  Below you hangs the beautiful fields of
Earth, looking fragile and far away, but full of hope.  A sense of
wistful regret touches you, as you think about what might have been,
and what will be.
10096.name: The Surface of the Moon

description:
Before you stands a monster.  Roughly 200 feet tall, it dwarfs even
the most massive titan.  Its purple and green armor, forming harsh
edges from its body, covers the massive form.  Glowing, dull yellow
eyes peek out from behind its mask, and its fists work idly, almost as
if in anticipation of something.
